-- Taiwan Stocks: Advanced Semiconductor, Formosa Sumco, Hiwin
-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 2012-02-03T05:48:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-03/taiwan-stocks-advanced-semiconductor-formosa-sumco-hiwin.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 0.3 percent to 7,674.99, the seventh
day of gains and the longest winning streak since December 2010.
The benchmark index has risen 6.1 percent this week, the most
since May 2009.  Advanced Semiconductor Engineering Inc. (2311)  (2311 TT) slide for
a third day, losing 1.4 percent to NT$27.80. The chip testing
and packaging company was cut to “neutral” from “add” at
Fubon Securities Co.  Formosa Sumco Technology Corp. (3532)  (3532 TT) surged 6.9 percent
to NT$37.20,  the highest close since Sept. 2. Parent Sumco
Corp. will move part of its production to Taiwan, R.S. Chao,
spokesman for Formosa Sumco, said by phone yesterday.  Hiwin Technologies Corp. (2049)  (2049 TT) retreated 3.1 percent to
NT$279, the most since Jan. 9. January sales fell 19 percent to
NT$764 million from a year earlier, according to a statement
filed to the Taiwan Stock Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
